# Performance and Optimization

## Core Web Vitals Targets

| Metric | Target | Measured By |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) | < 2.5s | Vercel Analytics (free) |
| INP (Interaction to Next Paint) | < 200ms | Vercel Analytics |
| CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift) | < 0.1 | Vercel Analytics |
| TTFB (Time to First Byte) | < 800ms | Vercel Analytics |

## Rendering Strategy

- **Static (SSG)** — public pages, marketing, docs (build-time generation)
- **Server (SSR)** — personalized dashboard views, search results
- **Client** — only for real-time interactive widgets (drag-drop, live previews)
- Default to server components; add `"use client"` only when hooks or browser APIs are needed

## Bundle Optimization

- **Max first-load JS**: < 100kB per route (check with `next build` output)
- Dynamic imports for heavy components: `next/dynamic` with `{ ssr: false }` for client-only
- Tree-shake icons: import individually (`import { Upload } from "lucide-react"`)
- No full library imports — always destructure (`import { clsx }` not `import clsx from "clsx"`)
- Analyze bundle periodically: `@next/bundle-analyzer`

## Image and Asset Optimization

- All images via `next/image` with `width`, `height`, `alt`, and `priority` on above-fold
- Use WebP/AVIF formats where possible (Next.js auto-optimizes)
- Lazy load below-fold images (default Next.js behavior)
- Fonts via `next/font` — zero layout shift, self-hosted, preloaded

## Data Fetching

- Fetch in server components as close to where data is used as possible
- Use React `cache()` for deduplicating identical requests within a render
- Set appropriate `revalidate` intervals — stale-while-revalidate for non-critical data
- Paginate all list queries — never fetch unbounded result sets
- Supabase queries: select only needed columns, use `.range()` for pagination

## Caching Layers

```
Browser cache (static assets, fonts)
  → CDN / Edge (Vercel, static + ISR pages)
    → Server (React cache, fetch cache)
      → Database (Supabase connection pooling)
```

- Static assets: immutable cache headers (Vercel default for `_next/static/`)
- API responses: `Cache-Control` headers based on data freshness needs
- Avoid caching user-specific or sensitive data at the CDN layer

## Performance Checklist (Per Feature)

- [ ] No layout shift — all dynamic content has reserved space
- [ ] Images optimized and lazy-loaded
- [ ] Heavy components dynamically imported
- [ ] List endpoints paginated
- [ ] No N+1 query patterns in server components
- [ ] Route segment size under 100kB first-load JS
